"Written evidence submitted by David Mackenzie&#xa0;\nI wholly support the stance and recommendations of the briefing paper “Towards a comprehensive land reform agenda for Scotland” (\nJames Hunter, Peter Peacock, Andy Wightman and Michael \nFoxley\n).\n&#xa0;\nIn particular I support:\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nI am writing as an ordinary citizen we believes that the land is not only our key asset but o\nur major responsibility for the present and the future.\n \nThe control of this asset and the discharge of the responsibility are severely distorted by the current pattern of formal ownership. This has to change.\n&#xa0;\nOctober 2013\n&#xa0;\n"